  "prompt": "Why does Quora mobile app use so much data?",
  "response": "Quora mobile app can consume a significant amount of data due to several reasons:\n\n1. Continuous content loading\n- Infinite scrolling feature loads new content automatically\n- High-resolution images and videos in answers\n- Preloading content in background\n\n2. Rich media content\n- Multiple images per answer\n- Embedded videos\n- Graphics and infographics\n\n3. Frequent background syncing\n- Updating feeds\n- Checking notifications\n- Refreshing recommended content\n\n4. Auto-play features\n- Videos that start playing automatically\n- Animated content\n\n5. Personalized recommendations\n- Algorithm constantly fetching and suggesting content\n- Tracking user interactions and preferences\n\n6. High-quality image resolution\n- Default settings might prioritize image quality over data efficiency\n\nTips to reduce data usage:\n- Enable data saver mode in app settings\n- Disable auto-play for videos\n- Limit background data refreshing\n- Download content when on Wi-Fi\n- Reduce image quality settings\n\nIf data consumption remains high, you might want to contact Quora support or consider alternative apps with more data-efficient designs.",
